Lagrange interpolation formula¶

use the Lagrange interpolation formula to construct the polynomial of smallest degree whose graph contains the following points.

In [106]:
x = [-2,-1,1,3]
y = [3,-6,0,-2]
f = lagrange(x, y)
In [107]:
f
Out[107]:
poly1d([-1.,  2.,  4., -5.])
In [108]:
f[0]
Out[108]:
-5.0
In [109]:
p = Polynomial(f.coef[::-1])
p
Out[109]:
$x \mapsto \text{-5.0} + \text{4.0}\,x + \text{2.0}\,x^{2} - \text{1.0}\,x^{3}$
In [110]:
x_new = np.arange(-2, 3.1, 0.1)
In [111]:
fig = plt.figure(figsize = (20,8))
plt.plot(x_new, p(x_new), 'b',x,y,'ro')
plt.title('Lagrange Polynomial')
plt.grid()
plt.xlabel('x')
plt.ylabel('y')
plt.show()
